description:
**IT Engineer (Contract Role for 6 Months)** 










**The Role:** 




 We are looking for an IT Engineer to maintain, upgrade and manage our software, hardware and networks. You will be responsible for supporting and maintaining Client operating systems \\- Mac, Windows. General maintenance of all IT\\-related hardware/software. The position provides exposure to a broad range of IT\\-related projects and activities.




 Your goal will be to provide effective IT assistance across all aspects of the business and ensure that our technology infrastructure runs smoothly and efficiently.










**Roles and Responsibilities:** 



* Ensures that the technologies are updated with current, stable, and compliant architecture and applications that meet enterprise standards.
* Manages system/application environment and ongoing operations;
* Performs on\\-call activities as needed for the environment and technologies;
* Contribute input to infrastructure architecture;
* Provide input into infrastructure architecture designs;
* Researches, designs, implements and tests technology solutions;
* Collaborates with IT and business area partners on work groups and initiatives;
* Troubleshoots software and/or hardware issues/failures;
* Ensures execution and alignment to architectural standards and blueprints;
* Resolves alerts and performs remediation activities;
* Writes programming/scripting;
* Determines migration and upgrade impacts and diagnose/resolve complex technology/application errors;
* Performs installation, monitoring, testing, configuration, migration, maintenance and troubleshooting of assigned technology (MAC);
* Proactively monitors and reports performance and utilization of assigned technologies;
* Assists with developing tactical strategies, processes and procedures related to systems/application administration.


- 


**Mandatory Qualifications:** 



* Experience analysing business requirements and translating them into technical solutions;
* 2 \\+ Years of experience of hands\\-on experience in HelpDesk, IT administration.
* Experience using Agile methodology;
* Ability to manage tasks independently and take ownership of responsibilities;
* Ability to adapt to a rapidly changing environment;
* Ability to communicate technical information clearly and articulately;
* Competent working in one or more environments highly integrated with an operating system (MAC and Windows ).;
* Must have strong Apple product knowledge;
* High critical thinking skills to evaluate alternatives and present solutions that are consistent with business objectives and strategy;
* Extensive working knowledge of multiple technologies and their interfaces and integration;
* Ability to learn from mistakes and apply constructive feedback to improve performance









**Location:** 
**Mumbai**
